    {
      "id": "5b4fb9fd_60e2d14b",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/dcaegen2-services/components/dcae-ms-healthcheck/templates/deployment.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 69,
      "message": "In the very first release where we used Kubernetes, I set up the charts to be able to use a separate namespace.  The idea wasn't accepted, and so we never used it.  As the charts evolved, we didn't consistently maintain the idea of a separate namespace for DCAE, so I'm not sure it would work today.  \n\nObviously I like the idea of a separate namespace. We need an ONAP-wide approach to doing it. The main issues are DNS (to access services in other namespaces--DCAE needs DMaaP and Consul, for example), which is pretty easy to solve, and possibly access to information contained in configMaps and secrets in other namespaces.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 511,
        "name": "Jack Lucas",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jflos@sonoris.net",
        "username": "jackl"
      },
      "updated": "2021-02-22 15:37:20.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "63b24325_0845464c",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "01cb9f24_6960e98f",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/dcaegen2-services/components/dcae-ms-healthcheck/templates/deployment.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 76,
      "message": "It's used by the healthcheck to find components that were deployed by Cloudify.  (The Cloudify plugin sets a label on each k8s Deployment and Service that it creates.  This connects Cloudify's view of what it deployed with the k8s view.) \n\nWe already have a dcaegen2 healthcheck that looks for these components, so we don't the dcaegen2-services healthcheck to look for them as well.  So I've removed this environment variable.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 511,
        "name": "Jack Lucas",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jflos@sonoris.net",
        "username": "jackl"
      },
      "updated": "2021-02-22 15:37:20.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "0a3573e1_bc96f799",
      "unresolved": false
    },
