    {
      "id": "44c7b4a9_64ad19db",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/dcaegen2-services/common/dcaegen2-services-common/templates/_deployment.tpl",
      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 95,
      "message": "With such defined template we have lost the ability to enroll certificate from CMPv2 server :(",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5775,
        "name": "Pawel Baniewski",
        "display_name": "Pawel Baniewski",
        "email": "pawel.baniewski@nokia.com",
        "username": "baniewsk"
      },
      "updated": "2021-02-22 16:04:13.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "860a31e5_66c19d50",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/dcaegen2-services/common/dcaegen2-services-common/templates/_deployment.tpl",
      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 95,
      "message": "For this release, I did not include the external cert capability.  I am planning to add that capability.  I have not looked at it in detail, but probably it involves more than just the image name here.\n\nIn this release, we are not losing the ability to deploy via Cloudify, so I someone wants a deployment of a component using an external cert, that is still possible.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 511,
        "name": "Jack Lucas",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jflos@sonoris.net",
        "username": "jackl"
      },
      "updated": "2021-02-22 18:41:00.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "44c7b4a9_64ad19db",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "a5629e9f_80de71ea",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/dcaegen2-services/components/dcae-tcagen2/values.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 103,
      "message": "This is a password used to access A&AI.  Apparently this password is agreed between AAI and DCAE in advance.  It appears that A&AI creates a hash for this password and puts the hash into resource files in the AAI charts (aai/components/{aai-resources, aai-traversal, aai-graphadmin, aai-schema-service}/resources/config/realm.properties). \n\nIdeally we would follow the model used elsewhere in OOM: the password would be derived at deployment time from a master password and stored into a secret that could then be used to populate both the A&AI configurations and the DCAE configuration.  Since we don't have that in this release, I propose keeping this as is for now.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 511,
        "name": "Jack Lucas",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jflos@sonoris.net",
        "username": "jackl"
      },
      "updated": "2021-02-23 00:03:09.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "85375750_965608e2",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "9d5cb7b4_f59ff4f2",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/dcaegen2-services/components/dcae-hv-ves-collector/requirements.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 1,
      "line": 27,
      "message": "I think my proposed approach won't work because while it builds the common subdirectory first, the resulting package isn't pushed to the repo immediately, and so the other components won't be able to pull it.\nHowever, just putting common as one of the components and making sure it's built first also does not seem to work.  I may be missing something, but because each component is a separate chart, I think each component needs to have common as an explicit requirement/dependency.  Either we need the 'file:' type of dependency, or we need to push the common chart to local before we build the others.\nDo you have an alternative suggestion?",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 511,
        "name": "Jack Lucas",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jflos@sonoris.net",
        "username": "jackl"
      },
      "updated": "2021-02-24 22:15:11.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "05d118d5_7ef99c35",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "497daada_5a83eb9a",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/dcaegen2-services/components/dcae-ves-collector/values.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 3,
      "line": 42,
      "message": "Please upgrade Ves version to 1.8.0",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 6482,
        "name": "Edyta Krukowska",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "edyta.krukowska@nokia.com",
        "username": "edyta"
      },
      "updated": "2021-02-25 12:30:00.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "9ac45de8_386298fb",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/dcaegen2-services/components/dcae-hv-ves-collector/values.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 7,
      "line": 90,
      "message": "While I don't strongly object to this change, I don't see any added benefit for security.  The plaintext password is still in the values.yaml file.  There is just more indirection.\nTHe proper solution for this is to change AAF to use derived passwords and store them into secrets that DCAE (and other AAF users) could access.\nPossibly adding the secret now will mean slightly less work in the future if the change is made to AAF, but apart from that I see no benefit and only added complexity.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 511,
        "name": "Jack Lucas",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jflos@sonoris.net",
        "username": "jackl"
      },
      "updated": "2021-03-08 18:14:40.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "a14fe321_0900d117",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/dcaegen2-services/components/dcae-hv-ves-collector/values.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 7,
      "line": 90,
      "message": "Ok so the benefit is very simple.\nEven through password is still hardcoded it can be changed by the user at the deployment time and the new password that user will set is going to be handled properly which means stored in secret and then in a file that is never written to the disk (emptyDir that resides in the memory)",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 4965,
        "name": "Krzysztof Opasiak",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "k.opasiak@samsung.com",
        "username": "kopasiak"
      },
      "updated": "2021-03-09 15:20:32.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "9ac45de8_386298fb",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "d1dddd08_f6c3a15c",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/dcaegen2-services/components/dcae-hv-ves-collector/values.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 7,
      "line": 90,
      "message": "It was possible previously to change the password at deployment time, since the password information was in values.yaml.  Your change makes no difference.  In the new version and in the previous version, it's necessary to change the passwords not only for the microservices but also (separately) for the servers that are authenticating them.  It takes coordinated changes in two places.\n\nAlso, the change you made is not working.  It doesn't pass verification.  It's probably a simple fix, but since the problem is three levels deep in the _secret template, it's not obvious to someone to who isn't familiar with the code.\n\nAs I said, I don't strongly object to this change (assuming we can get it to work), but I don't agree with the reasoning behind it. Too much added complexity, too little benefit in my view.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 511,
        "name": "Jack Lucas",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "jflos@sonoris.net",
        "username": "jackl"
      },
      "updated": "2021-03-09 16:07:42.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "a14fe321_0900d117",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
