      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "146be295_6e1fb97e",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/dcaegen2-services/components/dcae-hv-ves-collector/values.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 7,
      "line": 90,
      "message": "when the work is well done (and I agree, we're not there yet), the password would be set only at one place (by the server) and the clients would refer to the server's secret (as we're doing for databases for example).\n\nand with the way it's done, creds are only in the override (if you obviously change it ;) ) which is stored in a secret.\n\nBefore it would have been directly written into the config map, which is less secure",
      "author": {
